Mt. Cook for Easter. (South Island). -- Height of Delight for your Holidays. The cosy Hermitage (a fully-licensed hotel) is famous as the Alpine social centre. Take Nature's tonic in the Alpine Wonderland thousands of feet above worry level. Have the healthful happiness which lengthens life. See the greatest glaciers of the world's temperate zones. See the huge Hochstetter Ice-Fall. See the Marvellous Ice Caves which are like storied crystal palaces of fairyland. All manner of delightful side-trips amid enchanting scenes. Mount Cook, whose jewelled triple tiara gleams 12,349 ft. above the sea, one of the world's most majestic mountains, has a splendid retinue of noble peaks. Here, too, are stupendous glaciers far larger than the biggest “ice-rivers” of the Swiss Alps, and the way is easy to these huge courses of sparkling crystal. Everything in this bright realm of enchantment is on the gigantic scale: everything pleases; everything puts humanity on a high plane of exhilaration. -- Full details from Offices and Agencies. -- Mt. Mt. Cook (12,349 ft.), the Monarch of the Southern Alps, South Island, New Zealand. -- (Rly. Publicity ph -- What Emerson called “The frolic architecture of the snow” is responsible for some of the most beautiful scenes that greet the seeker after health in the mountains. In the above view we look out on Mt. Cook (the above picture is taken just behind the Hermitage) from a leafy bower that has been draped overnight so as to become a home for Santa Claus. It has been said that the finest of scenery can be seen from the Hermitage door. So all-comers, in whatever degree athletic or unathletie, have here their Mecca. -- “Above me are the Alps, -- The palaces of Nature, whose vast walls -- Have pinnacled in clouds their snowy scalps, -- And thron'd Eternity in icy halls -- Of cold sublimity, where falls and falls -- The avalanche--the thunderbolt of snow!” -- --Byeon

Take Nature's tonic in the Alpine Wonderland thousands of feet above worry level. Have the healthful happiness which lengthens life. See the greatest glaciers of the world's temperature zones. See the huge Hochstetter Ice-Fall. See the Marvellous Ice Caves which are like storied crystal palaces of fairyland. All manner of delightful side-trips amid enchanting scenes. Mount Cook, whose jawelled triple tiara gleams 12,349 ft. above the sea, one of the world's most majestic mountains, has a splendid retinue of noble peaks. Here, too, are stupendous glaciers far larger than the biggest “ice-rivers” of the Swiss Alps, and the way is easy to these huge courses of sparkling crystal. L'Auvergne et le Forez sous la Terreur. Les Martyrs de chez nous, par les abbés Gouttefangeas : Guillaume Carton, de la Renaudie... Jean-Marie Mollin, de Chalmazelle,... Pierre Bruyère, de Montbrison... Antoine Janvier, de Noirétable... Mathieu Roiret, de l'Hermitage... : Avec préface de Mgr. Lavallée...

Détails exacts d'un crime épouvantable commis dans un joli petit ermitage près la capitale, par une bande de scélérats qui ont assassiné et massacré le mari, la femme et la servante, à coups de poignard. Tourments et souffrances inouïes endurées par les victimes. Fidélité sans exemple de leur chien pour les venger. Lutte acharnée entre ce fidèle animal et les brigands, dont l'un a été horriblement étranglé, l'autre les jambes déchirées par morceaux ; un troisième a eu la tête broyée et les autres déchirés par lambeaux. Recherches faites sur les malfaiteurs et les aveux de celui qui a échappé à la fureur de l'animal ; sa condamnation à la peine de mort. [- Complainte à ce sujet.].
